      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-4">
          <h2>Focus</h2>
          <p>
            We wanted to make it easier for a student to focus on key learning activities: reading lecture notes, exploring lecture links, or completing lecture exercises. Because not all students are linear thinkers or linear learners we wanted to give them the option to explore different types of lecture content, grouped according to type.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
          <h2>Style Sheets</h2>
          <p>
            We also felt that it would be beneficial if students could select from a variety of stylesheets at the click of a button - and, at the end of COMP1950, add their own stylesheets in what could become an ongoing catalogue of more and more sheets to choose from. Eventually clicking on the stylesheet button would present a gallery of styles similar to CMS theme selection page, like Tumblr and Wordpress from which any number of styles could be tried out.
          </p>
       </div>
